t":"1342357259","lastUpdate":"2022-01-12T15:22:16.000Z","metadata":{"markets":["All"],"_id":"6671a1d87b8d8f101d6c0a19"},"search":["Engine - Installation","Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.","A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.","An unstable motorcycle may fall, causing injury to the operator or damage to the motorcycle.","While carefully locating the engine to the frame, attach the brake lines and harnesses to the brake line tidy as noted for removal.","Brake line (front brake master cylinder)","Brake line (front brake calipers)","Bluetooth connector","Rear brake light switch harness","Brake line (rear brake master cylinder)","Rear wheel ABS sensor","Align the engine mounting points with the corresponding positions on the frame.","Install and tighten the engine mounting bolts in the following 3 stages.","Stage 1","Insert the cylinder head left hand front mounting bolt with washer between the bolt and the frame.","Insert the cylinder head right hand front mounting bolt. Fit a new lock nut but do not fully tighten at this stage.","Fit the spacer between the crankcase and the frame on the right hand side. Insert the crankcase rear lower mounting bolt from the right hand side. Do not fit the washer and new lock nut at this stage.","Insert the crankcase rear upper mounting bolt from the right hand side. Do not fit the washer and new lock nut at this stage.","Insert the cylinder head rear mounting bolt and washer from the left hand side.","Stage 2","Partially withdraw the crankcase rear lower mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","service tool T3880377",". Refit the bolt and washer.","Partially withdraw the crankcase rear upper mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","service tool T3880377",". Refit the bolt and washer.","Counter hold the cylinder head front right hand mounting nut and tighten the bolt to ","24 Nm",".","Withdraw the cylinder head left hand mounting bolt and its washer, tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","service tool T3880377",". Insert the washer and bolt with washer between the bolt and the frame.","Withdraw the cylinder head rear mounting bolt and tighten the frame adjuster to ","5 Nm"," using ","service tool T3880377",".","Lower rear crankcase adjuster","Upper rear crankcase adjuster","Left hand cylinder head frame adjuster","Rear cylinder head frame adjuster","Swinging arm adjuster","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the crankcase lower rear mounting bolt. Counter hold the bolt and tighten the nut to ","80 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the crankcase upper rear mounting bolt. Counter hold the bolt and tighten the nut to ","80 Nm",".","Crankcase lower rear mounting bolt","Crankcase upper rear mounting bolt","Washer","Lock nut","Counter hold the nut and tighten the cylinder head front right hand mounting bolt to ","105 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the cylinder head front left hand mounting bolt. Counter hold the nut and tighten the bolt to ","105 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the cylinder head rear mounting bolt. Counter hold the nut and tighten the bolt to ","105 Nm",".","Cylinder head front right hand mounting bolt","Cylinder head front left hand mounting bolt","Cylinder head rear mounting bolt","Washer","Lock nut","Stage 3","Using ","service tool T3880104",", tighten the swinging arm pivot bolt adjuster sleeve to ","6 Nm",".","Fit the washer and a new lock nut to the swinging arm spindle. Counter hold the spindle and tighten the nut to ","110 Nm",".","Refit the swinging arm pivot cover to the left hand side of the frame.","On the left hand side, connect the engine ground cable.","Refit the rider’s left hand control plate, fit the upper fixing only and do not fully tighten at this stage.","Fixing","Left hand control plate","Refit the drive chain to the front sprocket and adjust (see ","Final Drive Chain Adjustment",").","Connect the oil pressure switch electrical connector.","Electrical connector","Do not allow a brake component to hang unsupported on the brake hose or line.","Brake hoses or lines that are not supported may become damaged or bent.","Bent or damaged brake hoses or lines lead to reduced braking efficiency causing loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","To prevent paint damage, do not spill brake fluid onto any area of the bodywork. Spilled brake fluid will damage paintwork.","Refit the rider’s right hand control plate, fit the upper fixing only and do not fully tighten at this stage.","Upper fixing","Right hand control plate","Refit the engine breather hose and secure with the hose clips.","Clips","Engine breather pipe","Route the alternator harness, crankshaft position sensor harness and starter motor leads as noted for removal.","Connect the starter motor lead to the starter motor solenoid and tighten the fixing to ","5 Nm",".","Connect the crankshaft position sensor to the main harness and attach the connector to the rear of the airbox.","Crankshaft position sensor electrical connector","Starter motor lead","Connect the alternator harness to the regulator/rectifier and refit the rear mudguard (see ","Rear Mudguard - Installation",").","On the right side of the airbox, connect the gear position sensor electrical connector to the main harness.","Gear position sensor electrical connector","Connect the clutch cable to the crankcase and clutch (see ","Clutch Cable - Installation",").","Ensure the mating surfaces on the inlet manifold and the cylinder head are clean.","Fit two new seals to the mating surfaces of the inlet manifold.","Fit the inlet manifold to the cylinder head.","Tighten the inlet manifold to cylinder head fixings to ","9 Nm"," in the sequence shown below.","Retighten the fixings one and two to ","9 Nm",".","Tightening Sequence","Ensure the throttle body hose is correctly fitted and tighten the clip to ","1.5 Nm",".","Connect the MAP hose and the evaporative emissions hose to the inlet manifold, as noted for removal.","Fit the mountings for the air intake finisher and tighten its fixings to ","3 Nm",".","Fixings","Mounting (right hand side shown)","Fit the air intake finishers and tighten the fixing to ","1.5 Nm",".","Fixing","Air intake finisher (right hand side shown)","Connect the following electrical connectors:","Coolant temperature sensor.","Fuel injectors ","Spark plug leads","Refit the coolant hose to the thermostat housing and secure using ","service tool T3880207",".","Refit the side panels (see ","Side Panels",").","Refit the exhaust catalytic system (see ","Exhaust Silencer - Installation",", ","Left Hand Header Pipe - Installation"," and ","Right Hand Header Pipe Assembly - Installation",").","Refit the cradle assemblies (see ","Cradle Assemblies - Installation",").","Tighten the rider’s right hand control plate upper fixing to ","25 Nm",".","Upper fixing","Right hand control plate","Refit the right hand heel guard and tighten its fixings to ","7 Nm",".","Fixings ","Heel guard","Tighten the rider’s left hand control plate upper fixing to ","25 Nm",".","Fixing","Left hand control plate","Perform the following operations:","Front Sprocket Cover - Installation","Coolant Expansion Tank - Installation","Evaporative Canister (if fitted) - Installation","Radiator - Installation","Sump Guard - Installation","Fuel Tank - Installation","Battery - Installation","Seat - Installation","If required, refill the engine with engine oil - ","Engine Oil and Filter Renew","Reset the neutral position adaption (see ","Neutral Position Adaption",")."],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-06-18T15:03:52.959Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-18T15:03:52.959Z","__v":0}